1773966070607028	msh-dev	itc:v3:AWLzMzyc5k_JEAAAAAAAQfbb13a_UAAAAAEtRg		item.update	bn-3si	{"field":"description","value":"Research and prototype creating a wgpu device + offscreen render target without a window surface. wgpu can create devices without a surface — render to a texture directly, then read back via buffer mapping. Key questions: can we reuse MeshRenderer with a non-surface texture? Can we skip the winit event loop entirely? Document findings and estimate effort."}	blake3:M-o5u1GJnlr4Qv03tpIwOQkqtLgO8gx8soE604_2aGs
1773966074222892	msh-dev	itc:v3:AWLzMzyc5k_JEAAAAAAAQfbb13a_UAAAAAEtRw		item.update	bn-3gc	{"field":"description","value":"If headless is feasible: add a 'render' subcommand to main.rs that takes model path, output path, and all rendering options (or --preset). Creates wgpu device without a window surface, loads mesh, applies settings, renders one frame to offscreen texture, reads back to PNG via buffer mapping, exits. Reuse MeshRenderer as much as possible."}	blake3:aTiWIyheeDv4g28MSsvWeTvcnhmIqUn67--OfrJHcOA
1773966076599465	msh-dev	itc:v3:AWLzMzyc5k_JEAAAAAAAQfbb13a_UAAAAAEtSA		item.update	bn-m9u	{"field":"description","value":"If headless is deferred: document the exact scripted workflow for using msh view --remote --preset sprite-bake for automation. Cover: startup and readiness detection, load model, apply preset, set camera, screenshot, quit. Provide a shell script example that command-lattice can use as a reference. Note: screenshots already work on the wgpu/main branch."}	blake3:bOtOoCLCIRkbwifeB1nKtFc71DwlID7suck0GGkRxVw
