1773967431501823	command-lattice-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkyTOeZ5M5QAAAAAAQa61bvb1ugAAAAEvAQ		item.create	bn-9r8	{"description":"## Problem\n\nWhen switching to orthographic projection (via `--projection ortho`, `--preset sprite-bake`, or RPC `set_projection(\"ortho\", ...)`), the mesh disappears entirely. Only the clear color is rendered. Perspective projection works fine with the same camera and mesh.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`camera.rs:71` uses `na::Matrix4::new_orthographic(...)` which produces an OpenGL-style projection matrix mapping depth to [-1, 1] NDC. wgpu expects [0, 1] depth range (Vulkan/Metal/DX12 convention). The linear z mapping in ortho means roughly half the depth range falls outside [0, 1] and gets clipped. Perspective works because the nonlinear w-divide handles the mapping differently.\n\n## Repro\n\n```bash\n# Works (perspective):\nmsh view test.obj --clear-color 0.2,0.2,0.2,1.0\n\n# Broken (ortho) — dark bg, no mesh visible:\nmsh view test.obj --projection ortho --ortho-height 50 --shading flat --clear-color 0.2,0.2,0.2,1.0\n```\n\n## Fix\n\nRemap the ortho projection z from [-1,1] to [0,1]. Either:\n- Post-multiply a z-remap matrix: `z' = z * 0.5 + 0.5`\n- Or build a custom ortho matrix directly targeting [0,1] depth\n\nThis is blocking the `sprite-bake` preset which the `command-lattice` sprite_gen pipeline depends on.","kind":"bug","title":"Orthographic projection doesn't render mesh — depth convention mismatch"}	blake3:o6QM74yDMl31IsvPUOHjsiqaLcKMkccgZdnXvLpYqP0
1773967437646112	command-lattice-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkyTOeZ5M5QAAAAAAQa61bvb1ugAAAAEvAg		item.create	bn-hmu	{"description":"## Problem\n\nThe `msh remote set-clear-color` subcommand expects a single string argument but the RPC method `set_clear_color` takes 4 separate floats (r, g, b, a). The CLI subcommand doesn't match either convention cleanly — it errors when passed 4 separate args:\n\n```\n$ msh remote set-clear-color 0.1 0.1 0.1 1.0\nerror: unexpected argument '0.1' found\n\nUsage: msh remote set-clear-color <COLOR>\n```\n\n## Expected\n\nShould accept either:\n- `msh remote set-clear-color 0.1,0.1,0.1,1.0` (comma-separated like `--clear-color` on `view`)\n- Or `msh remote set-clear-color 0.1 0.1 0.1 1.0` (4 positional args)\n\nCurrently unclear what format `<COLOR>` expects since neither works intuitively.\n\n## Context\n\nDiscovered while testing the RPC flow for the sprite_gen baking pipeline.","kind":"bug","title":"remote set-clear-color CLI takes wrong argument format"}	blake3:9bqSqUXv48FfETcH_Cx_Hkzg0SczhdFKFjEHXFyWe6Q
